136
00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:45.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We can use them to bring back anything
that doesn't belong there.

137
00:11:46.414 --> 00:11:48.290 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If anybody asks where you went,
what should I tell them?

138
00:11:48.374 --> 00:11:51.377 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
With two shuttlepods in the bay,
it'll be hard to explain.

139
00:11:52.711 --> 00:11:54.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm sure you'll think of something.

140
00:11:55.005 --> 00:11:57.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Try to stay out of trouble.
-You too.

141
00:11:57.591 --> 00:11:59.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here's the duty roster.

142
00:12:11.063 --> 00:12:13.232 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We just traveled 90 light-years
back to Earth.

143
00:12:13.315 --> 00:12:16.152 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And 150 years into the past.

144
00:12:17.862 --> 00:12:20.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Forgive me if I'm not entirely convinced.

145
00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:24.118 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You will be.

146
00:12:24.201 --> 00:12:25.786 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
