( beeping )

148
00:12:35.421 --> 00:12:38.257 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
This one has a motion-activated
security system.

149
00:12:39.341 --> 00:12:40.551 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeping )

150
00:12:41.677 --> 00:12:43.721 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This one too.

151
00:12:43.804 --> 00:12:45.764 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( chirping )

152
00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:56.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're in.

153
00:12:57.735 --> 00:12:59.069 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This apparatus...

154
00:13:01.155 --> 00:13:04.366 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It appears to have been designed
to incapacitate the vehicle.

155
00:13:12.833 --> 00:13:15.419 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeping, chirping )

156
00:13:25.554 --> 00:13:26.889 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( barking )

157
00:13:45.741 --> 00:13:47.076 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( door unlocks )

158
00:13:56.752 --> 00:13:59.755 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MAN ON RADIO: <i>Sunday! Sunday! Sunday!</i>
<i>At the tri-city speedway!</i>

159
00:13:59.838 --> 00:14:03.509 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>An all-star lineup of all your</i>
<i>favorite monster mayhem...</i>

160
00:14:03.592 --> 00:14:04.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( radio turns off )

161
00:14:07.137 --> 00:14:10.224 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Have you ever operated a vehicle
from this period?

162
00:14:11.183 --> 00:14:12.518 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I can pilot a starship.

163
00:14:19.066 --> 00:14:21.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"R", "N", "D", 2, 3, 4...

164
00:14:21.443 --> 00:14:24.029 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I suggest you begin with 2.

165
00:14:29.493 --> 00:14:31.287 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Foot controls.

166
00:14:31.370 --> 00:14:32.705 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeping )

167
00:14:46.468 --> 00:14:49.513 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't believe you've activated
your external lighting.

168
00:14:57.563 --> 00:15:00.774 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What year is that map from?
-2002.

169
00:15:00.858 --> 00:15:03.986 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
It was the closest I could find
in the Starfleet database.

170
00:15:04.069 --> 00:15:07.656 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The layout shouldn't have
changed a lot in two years.

171
00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:10.117 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Turn starboard on 24th street.

172
00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:13.871 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If that thing has a scanning radius
of three kilometers,

173
00:15:13.954 --> 00:15:16.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
how far are we gonna have
to drive to cover the entire city?

174
00:15:17.041 --> 00:15:21.879 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I've created a search grid that requires
a journey of approximately 80 kilometers.

175
00:15:21.962 --> 00:15:25.090 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it's probable we'll find them
before we complete it.

176
00:15:36.352 --> 00:15:38.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's that icon?

177
00:15:38.479 --> 00:15:41.315 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's a gasoline pump. We need to get fuel.

178
00:15:41.398 --> 00:15:44.360 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Where?
-Where isn't the problem.

179
00:15:45.402 --> 00:15:47.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We're going to need money. U.S. currency.

180
00:15:47.947 --> 00:15:50.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That's going to be difficult
at this time of night.

181
00:15:52.368 --> 00:15:53.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Not necessarily.

182
00:15:55.496 --> 00:15:57.122 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeping )

183
00:16:00.084 --> 00:16:02.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( teller machine whirs, beeps )

184
00:16:05.005 --> 00:16:07.549 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
People used to go to jail for this.

185
00:16:07.633 --> 00:16:10.094 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We'll return what we don't use.

186
00:16:17.518 --> 00:16:19.269 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

187
00:16:33.325 --> 00:16:34.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( doorbell rings )

188
00:16:42.209 --> 00:16:44.086 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Yeah?
-Are you Lawrence Strode?

189
00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:46.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Who are you?
-I'm from the blood bank.

190
00:16:46.755 --> 00:16:47.965 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We had a screw-up this afternoon.

191
00:16:48.048 --> 00:16:49.258 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We gave you the wrong papers to sign.

192
00:16:49.341 --> 00:16:50.843 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'm not giving the money back.

193
00:16:50.926 --> 00:16:53.012 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
No, no, no, no, no.
They don't want the money back.

194
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:54.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
In fact, they're gonna pay you again.

195
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:56.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
25 bucks.

196
00:16:56.765 --> 00:16:58.726 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They just need you
to sign the right papers.

197
00:16:58.809 --> 00:17:01.061 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Did you bring them?
-No, they wouldn't let me.

198
00:17:01.145 --> 00:17:02.896 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You got to do it
in front of the supervisor.

199
00:17:02.980 --> 00:17:04.982 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You know, the fat broad who paid you?

200
00:17:05.065 --> 00:17:06.442 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They sent me to drive you down.

201
00:17:07.192 --> 00:17:08.944 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-It's 11:00 at night.
-Yeah, I know.

202
00:17:09.028 --> 00:17:10.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They want to send your blood work out
first thing in the morning,

203
00:17:11.071 --> 00:17:13.574 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
and they can't do it
without the right paperwork.

204
00:17:15.909 --> 00:17:17.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You want the 25 bucks or not?

205
00:17:17.661 --> 00:17:19.413 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( indistinct talking on television )

206
00:17:22.166 --> 00:17:23.584 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( chain unlatches )

207
00:17:28.213 --> 00:17:31.550 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is this gonna take long?
I don't want to miss <i>Conan.</i>

208
00:17:32.760 --> 00:17:34.344 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Were they aware at this time

209
00:17:34.428 --> 00:17:37.639 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that Earth's supply of fossil fuel
was nearing depletion?

210
00:17:37.723 --> 00:17:40.350 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They had been for 30 years.

211
00:17:40.434 --> 00:17:42.936 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But it wasn't until 2061
that they finally--

212
00:17:43.020 --> 00:17:44.396 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeping )

213
00:17:44.480 --> 00:17:45.939 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
One kilometer, straight ahead.

214
00:18:10.714 --> 00:18:14.343 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Second structure from the left.
Three Xindi bio-signs.

215
00:18:14.426 --> 00:18:16.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Any humans?

216
00:18:16.178 --> 00:18:18.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Five. In another part of the building.

217
00:18:20.140 --> 00:18:22.476 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARCHER:
This doesn't look very residential.

218
00:18:26.146 --> 00:18:27.815 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Set your phase pistol to kill.

219
00:18:28.857 --> 00:18:31.735 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
When the reptilians boarded <i>Enterprise,</i>
stun had no effect.

220
00:18:36.490 --> 00:18:39.284 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
See what you can find out.
I'll look over there.

221
00:18:40.244 --> 00:18:43.080 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( communicator beeps )

222
00:18:43.163 --> 00:18:44.248 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Go ahead.

223
00:18:44.331 --> 00:18:47.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's a neutronic power source
coming from the first floor.

224
00:18:47.251 --> 00:18:50.170 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I found a gate
with an electric locking mechanism.

225
00:18:51.839 --> 00:18:53.674 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We shouldn't have a problem.

226
00:18:59.054 --> 00:19:00.681 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do you see the vehicle?

227
00:19:09.982 --> 00:19:10.983 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I see it.

228
00:19:13.318 --> 00:19:14.695 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( buzzes )

229
00:19:14.778 --> 00:19:15.863 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
MALE XINDI: <i>Yes?</i>

230
00:19:15.946 --> 00:19:17.239 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Loomis.
-( buzzes )

231
00:19:38.218 --> 00:19:40.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
MALE XINDI: Did you disinfect your hands?

232
00:19:41.638 --> 00:19:43.932 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I insert IVs all day. I told you that.

233
00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:47.060 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If there are any infections here,
it won't be because of me.

234
00:19:49.479 --> 00:19:50.772 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You forget something?

235
00:19:50.856 --> 00:19:52.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We've decided to compensate you

236
00:19:52.900 --> 00:19:56.236 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
for the final three patients
in one payment.

237
00:19:56.320 --> 00:19:58.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's not what we agreed.

238
00:19:58.614 --> 00:20:00.324 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You said I'd get paid for each one.

239
00:20:00.407 --> 00:20:04.494 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Bring us the last two blood types,
and you will be compensated.

240
00:20:05.287 --> 00:20:08.790 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We should wait a while.
A few more days at least.

241
00:20:08.874 --> 00:20:10.626 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
There was something on the news.

242
00:20:10.709 --> 00:20:13.587 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Cops are starting to get complaints
that people have gone missing.

243
00:20:13.670 --> 00:20:16.131 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We can't wait a few more days.

244
00:20:16.215 --> 00:20:18.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We need the last two.

245
00:20:18.217 --> 00:20:19.676 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Look, as soon as they figure out

246
00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:21.220 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that all these people here
have been to the clinic,

247
00:20:21.303 --> 00:20:23.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it won't take a rocket scientist
to point the finger at me.

248
00:20:23.805 --> 00:20:26.308 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Then I suggest
you finish your work quickly.

249
00:20:26.391 --> 00:20:28.769 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Look, I don't know
what you guys are up to,

250
00:20:28.852 --> 00:20:30.020 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
and I don't want to know.

251
00:20:30.103 --> 00:20:32.147 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not my business.

252
00:20:32.231 --> 00:20:35.484 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But the cops don't take kindly
to people who help terrorists.

253
00:20:35.567 --> 00:20:36.902 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I got to be real careful.

254
00:20:36.985 --> 00:20:39.571 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We will double your fee
for the final three.

255
00:20:39.655 --> 00:20:43.116 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
But the last two must be here by tomorrow.

256
00:20:43.617 --> 00:20:44.785 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Double?

257
00:20:47.913 --> 00:20:49.039 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Tomorrow?

258
00:20:49.665 --> 00:20:52.209 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah. All right.

259
00:20:52.292 --> 00:20:53.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I'll have them here by tomorrow.

260
00:21:04.471 --> 00:21:05.806 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Here he comes.

261
00:21:06.014 --> 00:21:07.474 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( car engine starts )

262
00:22:06.658 --> 00:22:07.951 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Ninth floor.

263
00:22:10.370 --> 00:22:12.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
280 pounds.

264
00:22:16.209 --> 00:22:18.420 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
William Myers.

265
00:22:19.379 --> 00:22:20.839 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Second floor.

266
00:22:21.757 --> 00:22:22.924 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( knock on door )

267
00:23:06.551 --> 00:23:08.095 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( grunts, gasps )

268
00:23:16.770 --> 00:23:18.688 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
And the man in the wheelchair?

269
00:23:19.314 --> 00:23:21.399 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why were you bringing him
to an abandoned factory

270
00:23:21.483 --> 00:23:22.734 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
in the middle of the night?

271
00:23:22.818 --> 00:23:24.611 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I swear, I don't know
what you're talking about.

272
00:23:25.821 --> 00:23:26.988 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's this?

273
00:23:28.865 --> 00:23:30.033 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh.

274
00:23:30.117 --> 00:23:32.369 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, I took that from the clinic.

275
00:23:32.452 --> 00:23:35.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I work at the blood bank on Porter Street.

276
00:23:35.372 --> 00:23:37.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Check with them. They'll tell you.
I've been there for over a year.

277
00:23:37.582 --> 00:23:40.836 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Why would you take it?
-Make a few extra bucks.

278
00:23:40.919 --> 00:23:43.046 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's plenty of people on the street
looking for that stuff.

279
00:23:43.130 --> 00:23:44.256 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Really?

280
00:23:45.173 --> 00:23:49.678 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why would anyone on the street
be interested in acquiring methohexital?

281
00:23:49.761 --> 00:23:51.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You make it a habit
of climbing out your window

282
00:23:51.972 --> 00:23:53.306 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
when someone knocks on the door?

283
00:23:53.390 --> 00:23:54.558 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't like cops.

284
00:23:57.769 --> 00:23:59.855 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Tell us about your friends
on Carpenter Street.

285
00:23:59.938 --> 00:24:02.482 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've never been to Carpenter Street.

286
00:24:02.566 --> 00:24:05.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You were there an hour ago
with a man in a wheelchair.

287
00:24:05.569 --> 00:24:07.612 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now tell me who's inside that factory.

288
00:24:07.696 --> 00:24:10.031 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you,
I don't know what you're talking about.

289
00:24:10.115 --> 00:24:12.242 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I think it's time you find me a lawyer.

290
00:24:15.328 --> 00:24:16.788 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Untie him.

291
00:24:18.123 --> 00:24:19.332 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You heard him.

292
00:24:19.916 --> 00:24:21.001 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Untie me.

293
00:24:29.676 --> 00:24:30.635 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( Loomis grunts )

294
00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:32.888 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's better.

295
00:24:33.847 --> 00:24:35.015 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( groans )

296
00:24:39.936 --> 00:24:41.229 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( panting )

297
00:24:42.939 --> 00:24:45.567 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I didn't feel right doing that
with you tied up.

298
00:24:46.526 --> 00:24:47.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Carpenter Street.

299
00:24:48.862 --> 00:24:51.281 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-You're not allowed to hit me.
-Untie him again.

300
00:24:51.364 --> 00:24:52.782 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, no, no, no!

301
00:24:52.866 --> 00:24:54.409 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Wait a minute!
Wait a minute! Wait a minute!

302
00:24:54.492 --> 00:24:55.827 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know who he is,
I swear to God.

303
00:24:55.911 --> 00:24:57.454 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A doctor, maybe.

304
00:24:57.537 --> 00:24:59.247 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Says he's working on a vaccine,
experimental.

305
00:24:59.331 --> 00:25:01.374 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He says he doesn't have approval
or something like that.

306
00:25:01.458 --> 00:25:03.460 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
So he needed me to bring him people.

307
00:25:03.543 --> 00:25:06.421 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does it seem logical to you
that legitimate medical research

308
00:25:06.504 --> 00:25:08.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
is being conducted
in an abandoned factory?

309
00:25:09.216 --> 00:25:11.176 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I thought about that.

310
00:25:11.259 --> 00:25:13.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Just tonight I thought maybe
he's some kind of a terrorist.

311
00:25:14.054 --> 00:25:17.849 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But I swear, if I knew that for a fact,
I never would have agreed to help him.

312
00:25:19.059 --> 00:25:23.188 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
In one individual, we've managed to find
the worst qualities of this era.

313
00:25:23.688 --> 00:25:28.443 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Greed. Violence. Moral corruption.

314
00:25:28.526 --> 00:25:30.946 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
But he said
he wasn't going to hurt anybody.

315
00:25:31.571 --> 00:25:34.115 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I just saw them an hour ago.
They were all OK.

316
00:25:34.449 --> 00:25:36.451 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-How many?
-Five.

317
00:25:36.534 --> 00:25:37.953 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, no, six.

318
00:25:38.036 --> 00:25:39.955 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
The wheelchair guy was number six.

319
00:25:40.038 --> 00:25:41.998 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
How did this "doctor" find you?

320
00:25:42.082 --> 00:25:44.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I told you I work at the blood bank.

321
00:25:44.584 --> 00:25:46.461 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
He wanted someone from every blood type.

322
00:25:46.544 --> 00:25:48.672 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Eight blood types, eight people.

323
00:25:48.755 --> 00:25:51.591 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He figured I had access
to that kind of information.

324
00:25:54.678 --> 00:25:56.554 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Did he also figure

325
00:25:56.638 --> 00:26:00.517 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
that you'd have no compunctions
about abducting people?

326
00:26:01.851 --> 00:26:03.144 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's he paying you?

327
00:26:04.020 --> 00:26:07.274 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
$5,000 apiece. Double for the last three.

328
00:26:07.357 --> 00:26:10.568 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Is that what human life is worth
in the 21st century?

329
00:26:11.903 --> 00:26:14.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I told you, he said he wasn't
going to hurt any of them.

330
00:26:15.615 --> 00:26:16.700 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What does he look like?

331
00:26:17.826 --> 00:26:20.829 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
He only calls me on the phone.
I saw him a couple of times,

332
00:26:20.912 --> 00:26:22.789 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
but he stays in the shadows.

333
00:26:22.872 --> 00:26:25.542 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, he's kind of tall.
That's all I can tell you.

334
00:26:26.209 --> 00:26:28.253 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why don't you let me go?

335
00:26:28.336 --> 00:26:30.547 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I swear to you, I will never do it again.

336
00:26:31.298 --> 00:26:33.341 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You are going to do it again.

337
00:26:34.217 --> 00:26:36.803 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
That is, if you have any hope
of staying out of prison.

338
00:26:36.886 --> 00:26:38.763 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What are you talking about?
-These two files...

339
00:26:38.847 --> 00:26:40.056 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"AB" positive and "B" negative.

340
00:26:40.140 --> 00:26:42.142 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-They're the final two?
-Yeah.

341
00:26:42.225 --> 00:26:43.852 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Well...

342
00:26:45.061 --> 00:26:47.063 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Then you're looking at your next victim.

343
00:26:47.731 --> 00:26:49.816 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A healthy male with "B" negative blood.

344
00:26:56.156 --> 00:26:58.533 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you think you're gonna
be in there a long time,

345
00:26:58.616 --> 00:27:00.994 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-we should get something to eat first.
-Be quiet.

346
00:27:01.077 --> 00:27:03.872 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Come on, I'm not...
I'm not talking about anything fancy.

347
00:27:03.955 --> 00:27:05.540 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A burger?

348
00:27:05.623 --> 00:27:07.167 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A taco?

349
00:27:08.460 --> 00:27:11.296 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
There's a drive-through
less than a mile from here.

350
00:27:12.297 --> 00:27:14.174 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Cops have to eat, don't they?

351
00:27:14.924 --> 00:27:17.052 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What is the matter with you two? I'll pay.

352
00:27:17.135 --> 00:27:18.762 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I told you to be quiet.

353
00:27:22.849 --> 00:27:24.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What side of the street is it on?

354
00:27:27.479 --> 00:27:29.898 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>Welcome to Burgerland.</i>
<i>How may I serve you today?</i>

355
00:27:29.981 --> 00:27:32.275 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I'll have the double superbeef,
no lettuce.

356
00:27:34.277 --> 00:27:37.489 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
One double superbeef without lettuce,
please.

357
00:27:37.572 --> 00:27:39.991 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>You can make that a triple</i>
<i>for only 40 cents extra.</i>

358
00:27:40.075 --> 00:27:41.368 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do it.

359
00:27:43.119 --> 00:27:45.038 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A double will be fine.

360
00:27:45.121 --> 00:27:46.581 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>Would you like</i>
<i>to make that a combo?</i>

361
00:27:46.664 --> 00:27:48.583 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah. Fries and a medium root beer.

362
00:27:48.666 --> 00:27:51.169 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>Will there be</i>
<i>anything else today?</i>

363
00:27:53.922 --> 00:27:56.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
A hamburger, ketchup only.

364
00:27:56.091 --> 00:27:58.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>You can make that a double</i>
<i>for only 40 cents extra.</i>

365
00:27:59.052 --> 00:28:00.178 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No, thank you.

366
00:28:00.261 --> 00:28:01.805 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Would you like to make that a combo?</i>

367
00:28:01.888 --> 00:28:03.723 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No. No combo.

368
00:28:03.807 --> 00:28:05.975 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>Will there be</i>
<i>anything else today?</i>

369
00:28:09.646 --> 00:28:12.732 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Does the fiesta salad
contain animal products?

370
00:28:12.816 --> 00:28:16.736 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
FEMALE: <i>No, but we can add three strips</i>
<i>of bacon for only 75 cents more.</i>

371
00:28:18.071 --> 00:28:19.739 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nothing for me, thank you.

372
00:28:19.823 --> 00:28:21.908 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-ARCHER: You sure?
-Quite.

373
00:28:33.378 --> 00:28:36.214 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You guys don't mind, do you? I'm starving.

374
00:28:37.298 --> 00:28:39.718 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You know, it'd make it a lot easier
if you'd untie my hands.

375
00:28:39.801 --> 00:28:41.970 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's not like I'm going anywhere.

376
00:28:42.053 --> 00:28:43.471 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Do the best you can.

377
00:28:46.850 --> 00:28:48.768 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Uh-oh. I told you.

378
00:28:50.186 --> 00:28:51.771 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let me get that for you.

379
00:28:51.855 --> 00:28:53.606 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Oh, boy.

380
00:29:00.989 --> 00:29:02.741 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You're a veggie. I forgot.

381
00:29:02.824 --> 00:29:05.034 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Why don't you take a fry?
They're probably OK.

382
00:29:09.414 --> 00:29:10.957 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have it your way.

383
00:30:04.219 --> 00:30:07.430 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
( whispers ) They'll come in to take
fresh blood samples every hour.

384
00:30:08.348 --> 00:30:12.018 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They readminister the sedative
every six hours.

385
00:30:12.685 --> 00:30:15.480 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I recommend you do whatever
you're gonna do before then.

386
00:30:15.563 --> 00:30:16.564 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( door opens )

387
00:30:20.860 --> 00:30:22.028 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Number seven.

388
00:30:22.111 --> 00:30:23.530 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Which one is it?

389
00:30:24.322 --> 00:30:25.824 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
"B"... "B" negative.

390
00:30:25.907 --> 00:30:28.159 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You'll have AB positive
by tomorrow night, I swear.

391
00:30:28.243 --> 00:30:29.911 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Make certain I do.

392
00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:54.477 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Engage the engine and proceed
to the second location.

393
00:30:54.561 --> 00:30:56.062 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Nice ray gun.

394
00:30:56.145 --> 00:30:58.273 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Am I supposed to believe that thing's
for real?

395
00:31:00.859 --> 00:31:01.901 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drive.

396
00:31:09.742 --> 00:31:13.538 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Ten grand apiece for the last three,
and I'm not gonna see a penny of it.

397
00:31:13.621 --> 00:31:16.499 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Don't speak until
we're out of visual range.

398
00:31:21.421 --> 00:31:24.173 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
MALE XINDI:
15 milliliters from the new arrival.

399
00:31:54.412 --> 00:31:56.873 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LOOMIS: You catch these guys
and I get immunity, right?

400
00:31:56.956 --> 00:31:59.000 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We're not talking about
copping to a lesser charge.

401
00:31:59.083 --> 00:32:01.753 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
T'POL: When my associate returns,
we'll discuss the details.

402
00:32:01.836 --> 00:32:03.588 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
LOOMIS:
Hey, I'm taking a big chance here, OK?

403
00:32:03.671 --> 00:32:07.133 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If your associate doesn't catch them,
they're gonna come looking for me, OK?

404
00:32:07.216 --> 00:32:09.093 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
You two better keep your word.

405
00:32:09.177 --> 00:32:12.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You've been abducting people for money,
and you're questioning our honesty?

406
00:32:40.750 --> 00:32:42.043 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sit back.

407
00:32:42.126 --> 00:32:44.545 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Relax. I'm just getting a smoke.

408
00:32:47.924 --> 00:32:49.050 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What are you doing?

409
00:32:50.426 --> 00:32:53.346 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I don't know about you, honey,
but I'm a little tense, know what I mean?

410
00:32:53.429 --> 00:32:55.181 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Extinguish that now.

411
00:32:55.264 --> 00:32:57.809 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
If you want some air, open your window.

412
00:32:59.602 --> 00:33:01.145 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Now.

413
00:33:03.523 --> 00:33:05.066 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( whirring )

414
00:33:41.310 --> 00:33:42.645 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( communicator beeps )

415
00:33:43.646 --> 00:33:45.231 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( keys jingling )

416
00:33:45.314 --> 00:33:47.233 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Stay exactly where you are.

417
00:33:57.410 --> 00:33:58.578 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
T'Pol.

418
00:33:58.661 --> 00:34:00.580 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>They brought</i>
<i>a bio-reactor with them.</i>

419
00:34:00.663 --> 00:34:02.665 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>They're synthesizing</i>
<i>some kind of viral agent.</i>

420
00:34:02.749 --> 00:34:04.625 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Rajiin warned us about a bio-weapon.

421
00:34:04.709 --> 00:34:06.044 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
This could be it.

422
00:34:06.127 --> 00:34:07.795 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why would they travel back through time?

423
00:34:07.879 --> 00:34:10.298 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARCHER: <i>Daniels said they might be</i>
<i>hiding from someone.</i>

424
00:34:10.381 --> 00:34:12.508 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
The past seems like
a pretty good place to hide.

425
00:34:12.842 --> 00:34:16.304 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>We've got to keep them</i>
<i>from getting it back to our time.</i>

426
00:34:16.387 --> 00:34:18.931 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Are you in a position
to disable all three of them?

427
00:34:19.015 --> 00:34:20.850 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know.

428
00:34:20.933 --> 00:34:22.685 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
I was thinking about trying
to take out the bio-reactor,

429
00:34:22.769 --> 00:34:25.104 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
but I could end up spreading
whatever's in there across half the city.

430
00:34:25.188 --> 00:34:27.440 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They must have some kind of
temporal beacon.

431
00:34:27.523 --> 00:34:29.942 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If you can destroy it,
they'll have no way of getting back.

432
00:34:30.026 --> 00:34:32.153 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got to find it first.

433
00:34:32.236 --> 00:34:34.614 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Modify your scanner
to a delta band frequency.

434
00:34:34.697 --> 00:34:36.157 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That should...

435
00:35:15.696 --> 00:35:16.906 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( yells )

436
00:35:50.106 --> 00:35:51.941 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They've gone out the west door.

437
00:35:53.151 --> 00:35:54.485 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They could be headed for the street.

438
00:35:56.737 --> 00:35:58.156 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They have the virus.

439
00:36:08.708 --> 00:36:10.126 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-T'Pol.
<i>-Yes, Captain.</i>

440
00:36:10.209 --> 00:36:11.878 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're in the west alleyway,
north of the main building.

441
00:36:11.961 --> 00:36:14.380 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
<i>-I could use some help.</i>
-Acknowledged.

442
00:36:17.842 --> 00:36:18.968 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drive.

443
00:36:19.677 --> 00:36:20.720 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Trouble?

444
00:36:21.596 --> 00:36:22.722 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drive.

445
00:36:42.742 --> 00:36:45.161 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Pull over and stop. Here.

446
00:36:48.539 --> 00:36:51.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Give you all that fancy equipment,
and what good does it do you?

447
00:36:51.542 --> 00:36:52.585 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Lower your window.

448
00:36:53.586 --> 00:36:55.546 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I knew your partner's plan wouldn't work.

449
00:36:56.589 --> 00:36:57.757 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Be quiet.

450
00:36:59.217 --> 00:37:00.301 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
They're coming.

451
00:37:09.018 --> 00:37:10.603 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-( honking )
-Stop!

452
00:37:31.374 --> 00:37:32.917 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( beeps )

453
00:37:38.506 --> 00:37:39.799 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on.

454
00:38:06.117 --> 00:38:07.743 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
ARCHER: He's trying to release the toxin.

455
00:38:10.288 --> 00:38:13.749 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
We've eliminated his only means
of returning to his own century.

456
00:38:13.833 --> 00:38:15.459 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Perhaps he has no other choice.

457
00:38:17.795 --> 00:38:19.255 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
ARCHER: If he's trying
to destroy humanity,

458
00:38:19.338 --> 00:38:21.007 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
he's not gonna be able to do it with that.

459
00:38:21.090 --> 00:38:23.426 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They only modified the virus
for six blood types.

460
00:38:23.509 --> 00:38:26.887 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
If they can infect
three-quarters of Earth's population,

461
00:38:26.971 --> 00:38:29.432 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
it's unlikely humans would pose
a threat to them in the future.

462
00:38:31.559 --> 00:38:33.352 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's hope he can't see in the dark.

463
00:38:34.520 --> 00:38:36.022 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Keep laying down fire.

464
00:38:41.235 --> 00:38:43.446 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( guns firing )

465
00:39:23.319 --> 00:39:25.696 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Don't move a muscle.
-( hisses )

466
00:39:26.280 --> 00:39:27.490 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Drop it.

467
00:39:32.912 --> 00:39:34.288 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Why a second weapon?

468
00:39:35.873 --> 00:39:37.792 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Where were you going to take it?

469
00:39:38.334 --> 00:39:42.213 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
We won't allow you to destroy us.

470
00:39:43.381 --> 00:39:45.966 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Your species is doomed.

471
00:40:12.159 --> 00:40:13.202 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Let's go.

472
00:40:19.458 --> 00:40:20.501 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Problem, sir?

473
00:40:22.878 --> 00:40:24.338 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
It's done.

474
00:40:24.422 --> 00:40:25.673 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Sir?

475
00:40:26.298 --> 00:40:28.300 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Archer to Lieutenant Reed.
-MALCOLM: <i>Go ahead.</i>

476
00:40:28.384 --> 00:40:30.386 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get a team down
to the command center on the double.

477
00:40:30.469 --> 00:40:31.470 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
<i>Aye, sir.</i>

478
00:40:31.554 --> 00:40:33.013 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Wait here for Malcolm.

479
00:40:33.097 --> 00:40:34.598 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Have everything brought to cargo bay 2.

480
00:40:34.682 --> 00:40:37.184 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I've got to get this to Phlox.

481
00:40:37.268 --> 00:40:39.854 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-What's going on?
-Come with me.

482
00:41:00.916 --> 00:41:02.877 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
( sirens wailing )

483
00:41:07.089 --> 00:41:09.758 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
-Get out of the car!
-He's on something.

484
00:41:09.842 --> 00:41:11.802 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Get out of the car!
Keep your hands where we can see them.

485
00:41:11.886 --> 00:41:13.262 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Come on. Come on.

486
00:41:13.345 --> 00:41:14.638 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
What's going on?

487
00:41:15.806 --> 00:41:17.766 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Hey, hey, hey, hey. I didn't do anything.

488
00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:19.310 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
OFFICER: We got a tip says you did.

489
00:41:19.393 --> 00:41:21.395 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
You're just lucky
all six of them are still alive.

490
00:41:21.479 --> 00:41:24.398 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
Those two cops that came to my place,
they offered me a deal.

491
00:41:24.482 --> 00:41:25.900 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
That's the only reason I helped them.

492
00:41:25.983 --> 00:41:27.401 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
I don't know what you're talking about.

493
00:41:27.485 --> 00:41:28.819 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Get him out of here.

494
00:41:28.903 --> 00:41:31.572 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Those creatures... The lizard people...

495
00:41:31.655 --> 00:41:33.949 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:79.33% 
They're around here somewhere.
You got to find them.

496
00:41:34.033 --> 00:41:35.618 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
No problem. We'll get right on that.

497
00:41:35.701 --> 00:41:37.912 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Be careful. Be careful. They got ray guns.

498
00:41:37.995 --> 00:41:40.164 position:50.00%,middle align:middle size:80.00% line:84.67% 
Yeah, ray guns. Got it. Watch your head.

